xt>&lt;p>Writing a biography of Max Weber using all the available scholarly sources is an immense challenge and a pressing requirement for a proper understanding of this many-sided social scientist. The Max Weber Gesamtausgabe has collected together 3,500 of his letters and is completing the publication of his writings in over 25 volumes. The Anglophone world still mainly relies on a narrow selections of his work without any comprehension of his overall output and the multi-disciplinarity of his interests. His letters give us real insights into the academic and political debates of his day as well as extensive accounts of his turbulent personal life. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The grant will make his correspondence more accessible, by placing parts of it on a database complete with full abstracts and catalogue details. A biography will be written that will provide a reliable chronology of his personal, academic and political life. It will also consider the role of his wife Marianne Weber, one of Germany?s first women politicians and gender theorists. The grant will also aid the publication and translation of some of his key works: initially, the ?Methodological Writings? and ?Economy and Society. The Final Version?. These editions will be equipped with a proper scholarly apparatus.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2010-01-31</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2008-02-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>168841</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs/><gtr:exploitationOutputs/><gtr:furtherFundingOutputs/><gtr:impactSummaryOutputs/><gtr:intellectualPropertyOutputs/><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">ES/F004303/1</gtr:identifier><gtr:identifier type="RES">RES-063-27-0094</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>541CDC75-F361-4961-9EFE-34B2C8ACE947</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>History</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>5D762B83-597E-4E91-B2F7-04CBB955175C</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>0</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Pol. sci. &amp; internat. studies<